      "role": "user",
      "content": "but the cut isnt that deep, its just open. and i read online that medical grade honey is actually better for wounds than some doctors use because it keeps it moist and kills bacteria naturally. if i just use a thick layer of honey and a really tight bandage, wouldnt that basically do the same thing as stitches by sealing it up? im just really trying to avoid the hospital bills if possible.",
